ifxbase
	- builds os env only.  used in conjunction with ifx2

ifx2
	- builds only informix
	- relies on ifxbase



To Build the Docker Image:
1.  cd ifxbase
2.  ./build
3.  cd ifx2
4.  ./build


To Start the Docker Image:
1.  ./runifx
	- This has two options, one does -it, the other does -td.
	- -it will be interactive.  Once you exit the shell it will take the engine down
	- -td will run the container in the background

2.  To attach to docker container
	docker exec -it <name> bash
		name = iif_developer_edition, iif_inovvator_c

